<paragraph blockId="120.[189,1399,1651,1888]" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">
The collector was presumably J.H. Wilhelm Baron (von) Nolcken, who collected in the mountains of 
<collectingCountry box="[225,341,1756,1782]" name="Colombia" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Colombia</collectingCountry>
in 
<date box="[387,494,1756,1782]" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" value="1870" valueMax="1871">1870–71</date>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Papavero" box="[509,709,1756,1783]" firstAuthor="Papavero" journalOrPublisher="Museu de Zoologica, Universidade de Sao Paulo" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" refId="ref59361" refString="Papavero N. 1973. Essays on the History of Neotropical Dipterology. Volume 2. Museu de Zoologica, Universidade de Sao Paulo." title="Essays on the History of Neotropical Dipterology. Volume 2" type="book" year="1973">Papavero (1973)</bibRefCitation>
provides a summary of Baron von Nolcken’s travels in 
<collectingCountry box="[189,308,1791,1817]" name="Colombia" pageId="120" pageNumber="121">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, naming several collecting localities of which three are recorded as above 
<quantity box="[1200,1294,1791,1818]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" unit="m" value="1500.0">1500 m</quantity>
: Ubaque (
<quantity box="[197,293,1827,1854]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.95" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" unit="m" value="1950.0">1950 m</quantity>
), Cuequeta (
<quantity box="[444,538,1827,1853]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" unit="m" value="2200.0">2200 m</quantity>
) and Hato (
<quantity box="[682,779,1827,1854]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="120" pageNumber="121" unit="m" value="1500.0">1500 m</quantity>
). Enderlein indicated that the von Nolcken material came from the H. Loew collection.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
